8 // ----
9 // This is an extremely simple MachineInstr-level copy propagation pass. ----
10 // ----
11 // This pass forwards the source of COPYs to the users of their destinations ----
12 // when doing so is legal. For example: ----
13 // ----
14 // %reg1 = COPY %reg0 ----
15 // ... ----
16 // ... = OP %reg1 ----
17 // ----
18 // If ----
19 // - %reg0 has not been clobbered by the time of the use of %reg1 ----
20 // - the register class constraints are satisfied ----
21 // - the COPY def is the only value that reaches OP ----
22 // then this pass replaces the above with: ----
23 // ----
24 // %reg1 = COPY %reg0 ----
25 // ... ----
26 // ... = OP %reg0 ----
27 // ----
28 // This pass also removes some redundant COPYs. For example: ----
29 // ----
30 // %R1 = COPY %R0 ----
31 // ... // No clobber of %R1 ----
32 // %R0 = COPY %R1 <<< Removed ----
33 // ----
34 // or ----
35 // ----
36 // %R1 = COPY %R0 ----
37 // ... // No clobber of %R0 ----
38 // %R1 = COPY %R0 <<< Removed ----
39 // ----
40 // or ----
41 // ----
42 // $R0 = OP ... ----
43 // ... // No read/clobber of $R0 and $R1 ----
44 // $R1 = COPY $R0 // $R0 is killed ----
45 // Replace $R0 with $R1 and remove the COPY ----
46 // $R1 = OP ... ----
47 // ... ----
48 // ----
49 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
50 ----

95 static std::optional isCopyInstr(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
96 const TargetInstrInfo &TII, ----
97 bool UseCopyInstr) { ----
98 if (UseCopyInstr) 0
99 return TII.isCopyInstr(MI); 0
100 ----
101 if (MI.isCopy()) 0
102 return std::optional( ----
103 DestSourcePair{MI.getOperand(0), MI.getOperand(1)}); 0
104 ----
105 return std::nullopt; 0
106 } ----

118 /// Mark all of the given registers and their subregisters as unavailable for ----
119 /// copying. ----
120 void markRegsUnavailable(ArrayRef Regs, 0
121 const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI) { ----
122 for (MCRegister Reg : Regs) { 0
123 // Source of copy is no longer available for propagation. ----
124 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI.regunits(Reg)) { 0
125 auto CI = Copies.find(Unit); 0
126 if (CI != Copies.end()) 0
127 CI->second.Avail = false; 0
128 } ----
129 } ----
130 } 0

132 /// Remove register from copy maps. ----
133 void invalidateRegister(MCRegister Reg, const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI, 0
134 const TargetInstrInfo &TII, bool UseCopyInstr) { ----
135 // Since Reg might be a subreg of some registers, only invalidate Reg is not ----
136 // enough. We have to find the COPY defines Reg or registers defined by Reg ----
137 // and invalidate all of them. ----
138 SmallSet RegsToInvalidate; 0
139 RegsToInvalidate.insert(Reg); 0
140 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI.regunits(Reg)) { 0
141 auto I = Copies.find(Unit); 0
142 if (I != Copies.end()) { 0
143 if (MachineInstr *MI = I->second.MI) { 0
144 std::optional CopyOperands = ----
145 isCopyInstr(*MI, TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
146 assert(CopyOperands && "Expect copy"); 0
147 ----
148 RegsToInvalidate.insert( 0
149 CopyOperands->Destination->getReg().asMCReg()); 0
150 RegsToInvalidate.insert(CopyOperands->Source->getReg().asMCReg()); 0
151 } ----
152 RegsToInvalidate.insert(I->second.DefRegs.begin(), 0
153 I->second.DefRegs.end()); 0
154 } ----
155 } ----
156 for (MCRegister InvalidReg : RegsToInvalidate) 0
157 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI.regunits(InvalidReg)) 0
158 Copies.erase(Unit); 0
159 } 0

161 /// Clobber a single register, removing it from the tracker's copy maps. ----
162 void clobberRegister(MCRegister Reg, const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI, 0
163 const TargetInstrInfo &TII, bool UseCopyInstr) { ----
164 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI.regunits(Reg)) { 0
165 auto I = Copies.find(Unit); 0
166 if (I != Copies.end()) { 0
167 // When we clobber the source of a copy, we need to clobber everything ----
168 // it defined. ----
169 markRegsUnavailable(I->second.DefRegs, TRI); 0
170 // When we clobber the destination of a copy, we need to clobber the ----
171 // whole register it defined. ----
172 if (MachineInstr *MI = I->second.MI) { 0
173 std::optional CopyOperands = ----
174 isCopyInstr(*MI, TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
175 markRegsUnavailable({CopyOperands->Destination->getReg().asMCReg()}, 0
176 TRI); ----
177 } ----
178 // Now we can erase the copy. ----
179 Copies.erase(I); 0
180 } ----
181 } ----
182 } 0

184 /// Add this copy's registers into the tracker's copy maps. ----
185 void trackCopy(MachineInstr *MI, const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI, 0
186 const TargetInstrInfo &TII, bool UseCopyInstr) { ----
187 std::optional CopyOperands = ----
188 isCopyInstr(*MI, TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
189 assert(CopyOperands && "Tracking non-copy?"); 0
190 ----
191 MCRegister Src = CopyOperands->Source->getReg().asMCReg(); 0
192 MCRegister Def = CopyOperands->Destination->getReg().asMCReg(); 0
193 ----
194 // Remember Def is defined by the copy. ----
195 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI.regunits(Def)) 0
196 Copies[Unit] = {MI, nullptr, {}, true}; 0
197 ----
198 // Remember source that's copied to Def. Once it's clobbered, then ----
199 // it's no longer available for copy propagation. ----
200 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI.regunits(Src)) { 0
201 auto I = Copies.insert({Unit, {nullptr, nullptr, {}, false}}); 0
202 auto &Copy = I.first->second; 0
203 if (!is_contained(Copy.DefRegs, Def)) 0
204 Copy.DefRegs.push_back(Def); 0
205 Copy.LastSeenUseInCopy = MI; 0
206 } ----
207 } 0

263 MachineInstr *findAvailCopy(MachineInstr &DestCopy, MCRegister Reg, 0
264 const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI, ----
265 const TargetInstrInfo &TII, bool UseCopyInstr) { ----
266 // We check the first RegUnit here, since we'll only be interested in the ----
267 // copy if it copies the entire register anyway. ----
268 MCRegUnit RU = *TRI.regunits(Reg).begin(); 0

271 ----
272 if (!AvailCopy) 0
273 return nullptr; 0

275 std::optional CopyOperands = ----
276 isCopyInstr(*AvailCopy, TII, UseCopyInstr); 0

279 if (!TRI.isSubRegisterEq(AvailDef, Reg)) 0
280 return nullptr; 0
281 ----
282 // Check that the available copy isn't clobbered by any regmasks between ----

408 void MachineCopyPropagation::ReadRegister(MCRegister Reg, MachineInstr &Reader, 0
409 DebugType DT) { ----
410 // If 'Reg' is defined by a copy, the copy is no longer a candidate ----
411 // for elimination. If a copy is "read" by a debug user, record the user ----
412 // for propagation. ----
413 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI->regunits(Reg)) { 0
414 if (MachineInstr *Copy = Tracker.findCopyForUnit(Unit, *TRI)) { 0
415 if (DT == RegularUse) { 0
416 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "MCP: Copy is used - not dead: "; Copy->dump()); 0
417 MaybeDeadCopies.remove(Copy); 0
418 } else { ----
419 CopyDbgUsers[Copy].insert(&Reader); 0
420 } ----
421 } ----
422 } ----
423 } 0
424 ----
425 /// Return true if \p PreviousCopy did copy register \p Src to register \p Def. ----
426 /// This fact may have been obscured by sub register usage or may not be true at ----
427 /// all even though Src and Def are subregisters of the registers used in ----
428 /// PreviousCopy. e.g. ----
429 /// isNopCopy("ecx = COPY eax", AX, CX) == true ----
430 /// isNopCopy("ecx = COPY eax", AH, CL) == false ----
431 static bool isNopCopy(const MachineInstr &PreviousCopy, MCRegister Src, 0
432 MCRegister Def, const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI, ----
433 const TargetInstrInfo *TII, bool UseCopyInstr) { ----
434 ----
435 std::optional CopyOperands = ----
436 isCopyInstr(PreviousCopy, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
437 MCRegister PreviousSrc = CopyOperands->Source->getReg().asMCReg(); 0
438 MCRegister PreviousDef = CopyOperands->Destination->getReg().asMCReg(); 0
439 if (Src == PreviousSrc && Def == PreviousDef) 0
440 return true; 0
441 if (!TRI->isSubRegister(PreviousSrc, Src)) 0
442 return false; 0
443 unsigned SubIdx = TRI->getSubRegIndex(PreviousSrc, Src); 0
444 return SubIdx == TRI->getSubRegIndex(PreviousDef, Def); 0
445 } ----
446 ----
447 /// Remove instruction \p Copy if there exists a previous copy that copies the ----
448 /// register \p Src to the register \p Def; This may happen indirectly by ----
449 /// copying the super registers. ----
450 bool MachineCopyPropagation::eraseIfRedundant(MachineInstr &Copy, 0
451 MCRegister Src, MCRegister Def) { ----
452 // Avoid eliminating a copy from/to a reserved registers as we cannot predict ----
453 // the value (Example: The sparc zero register is writable but stays zero). ----
454 if (MRI->isReserved(Src) || MRI->isReserved(Def)) 0
455 return false; 0
456 ----
457 // Search for an existing copy. ----
458 MachineInstr *PrevCopy = ----
459 Tracker.findAvailCopy(Copy, Def, *TRI, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
460 if (!PrevCopy) 0
461 return false; 0
462 ----
463 auto PrevCopyOperands = isCopyInstr(*PrevCopy, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
464 // Check that the existing copy uses the correct sub registers. ----
465 if (PrevCopyOperands->Destination->isDead()) 0
466 return false; 0
467 if (!isNopCopy(*PrevCopy, Src, Def, TRI, TII, UseCopyInstr)) 0
468 return false; 0
469 ----
470 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "MCP: copy is a NOP, removing: "; Copy.dump()); 0
471 ----
472 // Copy was redundantly redefining either Src or Def. Remove earlier kill ----
473 // flags between Copy and PrevCopy because the value will be reused now. ----
474 std::optional CopyOperands = ----
475 isCopyInstr(Copy, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
476 assert(CopyOperands); 0
477 ----
478 Register CopyDef = CopyOperands->Destination->getReg(); 0
479 assert(CopyDef == Src || CopyDef == Def); 0
480 for (MachineInstr &MI : 0
481 make_range(PrevCopy->getIterator(), Copy.getIterator())) 0
482 MI.clearRegisterKills(CopyDef, TRI); 0
483 ----
484 // Clear undef flag from remaining copy if needed. ----
485 if (!CopyOperands->Source->isUndef()) { 0
486 PrevCopy->getOperand(PrevCopyOperands->Source->getOperandNo()) 0
487 .setIsUndef(false); 0
488 } ----
489 ----
490 Copy.eraseFromParent(); 0
491 Changed = true; 0
492 ++NumDeletes; 0
493 return true; 0
494 } ----
495 ----
496 bool MachineCopyPropagation::isBackwardPropagatableRegClassCopy( 0
497 const MachineInstr &Copy, const MachineInstr &UseI, unsigned UseIdx) { ----
498 std::optional CopyOperands = ----
499 isCopyInstr(Copy, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
500 Register Def = CopyOperands->Destination->getReg(); 0
501 ----
502 if (const TargetRegisterClass *URC = 0
503 UseI.getRegClassConstraint(UseIdx, TII, TRI)) 0
504 return URC->contains(Def); 0
505 ----
506 // We don't process further if UseI is a COPY, since forward copy propagation ----
507 // should handle that. ----
508 return false; 0
509 } ----
510 ----
511 /// Decide whether we should forward the source of \param Copy to its use in ----
512 /// \param UseI based on the physical register class constraints of the opcode ----
513 /// and avoiding introducing more cross-class COPYs. ----
514 bool MachineCopyPropagation::isForwardableRegClassCopy(const MachineInstr &Copy, 0
515 const MachineInstr &UseI, ----
516 unsigned UseIdx) { ----
517 std::optional CopyOperands = ----
518 isCopyInstr(Copy, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
519 Register CopySrcReg = CopyOperands->Source->getReg(); 0
520 ----
521 // If the new register meets the opcode register constraints, then allow ----
522 // forwarding. ----
523 if (const TargetRegisterClass *URC = 0
524 UseI.getRegClassConstraint(UseIdx, TII, TRI)) 0
525 return URC->contains(CopySrcReg); 0
526 ----
527 auto UseICopyOperands = isCopyInstr(UseI, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
528 if (!UseICopyOperands) 0
529 return false; 0
530 ----
531 /// COPYs don't have register class constraints, so if the user instruction ----
532 /// is a COPY, we just try to avoid introducing additional cross-class ----
533 /// COPYs. For example: ----
534 /// ----
535 /// RegClassA = COPY RegClassB // Copy parameter ----
536 /// ... ----
537 /// RegClassB = COPY RegClassA // UseI parameter ----
538 /// ----
539 /// which after forwarding becomes ----
540 /// ----
541 /// RegClassA = COPY RegClassB ----
542 /// ... ----
543 /// RegClassB = COPY RegClassB ----
544 /// ----
545 /// so we have reduced the number of cross-class COPYs and potentially ----
546 /// introduced a nop COPY that can be removed. ----
547 ----
548 // Allow forwarding if src and dst belong to any common class, so long as they ----
549 // don't belong to any (possibly smaller) common class that requires copies to ----
550 // go via a different class. ----
551 Register UseDstReg = UseICopyOperands->Destination->getReg(); 0
552 bool Found = false; 0
553 bool IsCrossClass = false; 0
554 for (const TargetRegisterClass *RC : TRI->regclasses()) { 0
555 if (RC->contains(CopySrcReg) && RC->contains(UseDstReg)) { 0
556 Found = true; 0
557 if (TRI->getCrossCopyRegClass(RC) != RC) { 0
558 IsCrossClass = true; 0
559 break; 0
560 } ----
561 } ----
562 } ----
563 if (!Found) 0
564 return false; 0
565 if (!IsCrossClass) 0
566 return true; 0
567 // The forwarded copy would be cross-class. Only do this if the original copy ----
568 // was also cross-class. ----
569 Register CopyDstReg = CopyOperands->Destination->getReg(); 0
570 for (const TargetRegisterClass *RC : TRI->regclasses()) { 0
571 if (RC->contains(CopySrcReg) && RC->contains(CopyDstReg) && 0
572 TRI->getCrossCopyRegClass(RC) != RC) 0
573 return true; 0
574 } ----
575 return false; 0
576 } ----
577 ----
578 /// Check that \p MI does not have implicit uses that overlap with it's \p Use ----
579 /// operand (the register being replaced), since these can sometimes be ----
580 /// implicitly tied to other operands. For example, on AMDGPU: ----
581 /// ----
582 /// V_MOVRELS_B32_e32 %VGPR2, %M0, %EXEC, %VGPR2_VGPR3_VGPR4_VGPR5 ----
583 /// ----
584 /// the %VGPR2 is implicitly tied to the larger reg operand, but we have no ----
585 /// way of knowing we need to update the latter when updating the former. ----
586 bool MachineCopyPropagation::hasImplicitOverlap(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
587 const MachineOperand &Use) { ----
588 for (const MachineOperand &MIUse : MI.uses()) 0
589 if (&MIUse != &Use && MIUse.isReg() && MIUse.isImplicit() && 0
590 MIUse.isUse() && TRI->regsOverlap(Use.getReg(), MIUse.getReg())) 0
591 return true; 0
592 ----
593 return false; 0
594 } ----
595 ----
596 /// For an MI that has multiple definitions, check whether \p MI has ----
597 /// a definition that overlaps with another of its definitions. ----
598 /// For example, on ARM: umull r9, r9, lr, r0 ----
599 /// The umull instruction is unpredictable unless RdHi and RdLo are different. ----
600 bool MachineCopyPropagation::hasOverlappingMultipleDef( 0
601 const MachineInstr &MI, const MachineOperand &MODef, Register Def) { ----
602 for (const MachineOperand &MIDef : MI.defs()) { 0
603 if ((&MIDef != &MODef) && MIDef.isReg() && 0
604 TRI->regsOverlap(Def, MIDef.getReg())) 0
605 return true; 0
606 } ----
607 ----
608 return false; 0
609 } ----
610 ----
611 /// Look for available copies whose destination register is used by \p MI and ----
612 /// replace the use in \p MI with the copy's source register. ----
613 void MachineCopyPropagation::forwardUses(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
614 if (!Tracker.hasAnyCopies()) 0
615 return; 0
616 ----
617 // Look for non-tied explicit vreg uses that have an active COPY ----
618 // instruction that defines the physical register allocated to them. ----
619 // Replace the vreg with the source of the active COPY. ----
620 for (unsigned OpIdx = 0, OpEnd = MI.getNumOperands(); OpIdx < OpEnd; 0
621 ++OpIdx) { ----
622 MachineOperand &MOUse = MI.getOperand(OpIdx); 0
623 // Don't forward into undef use operands since doing so can cause problems ----
624 // with the machine verifier, since it doesn't treat undef reads as reads, ----
625 // so we can end up with a live range that ends on an undef read, leading to ----
626 // an error that the live range doesn't end on a read of the live range ----
627 // register. ----
628 if (!MOUse.isReg() || MOUse.isTied() || MOUse.isUndef() || MOUse.isDef() || 0
629 MOUse.isImplicit()) 0
630 continue; 0
631 ----
632 if (!MOUse.getReg()) 0
633 continue; 0
634 ----
635 // Check that the register is marked 'renamable' so we know it is safe to ----
636 // rename it without violating any constraints that aren't expressed in the ----
637 // IR (e.g. ABI or opcode requirements). ----
638 if (!MOUse.isRenamable()) 0
639 continue; 0
640 ----
641 MachineInstr *Copy = Tracker.findAvailCopy(MI, MOUse.getReg().asMCReg(), 0
642 *TRI, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
643 if (!Copy) 0
644 continue; 0
645 ----
646 std::optional CopyOperands = ----
647 isCopyInstr(*Copy, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
648 Register CopyDstReg = CopyOperands->Destination->getReg(); 0
649 const MachineOperand &CopySrc = *CopyOperands->Source; 0
650 Register CopySrcReg = CopySrc.getReg(); 0
651 ----
652 Register ForwardedReg = CopySrcReg; 0
653 // MI might use a sub-register of the Copy destination, in which case the ----
654 // forwarded register is the matching sub-register of the Copy source. ----
655 if (MOUse.getReg() != CopyDstReg) { 0
656 unsigned SubRegIdx = TRI->getSubRegIndex(CopyDstReg, MOUse.getReg()); 0
657 assert(SubRegIdx && 0
658 "MI source is not a sub-register of Copy destination"); ----
659 ForwardedReg = TRI->getSubReg(CopySrcReg, SubRegIdx); 0
660 if (!ForwardedReg) { 0
661 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "MCP: Copy source does not have sub-register " 0
662 << TRI->getSubRegIndexName(SubRegIdx) << '\n'); ----
663 continue; 0
664 } ----
665 } ----
666 ----
667 // Don't forward COPYs of reserved regs unless they are constant. ----
668 if (MRI->isReserved(CopySrcReg) && !MRI->isConstantPhysReg(CopySrcReg)) 0
669 continue; 0
670 ----
671 if (!isForwardableRegClassCopy(*Copy, MI, OpIdx)) 0
672 continue; 0
673 ----
674 if (hasImplicitOverlap(MI, MOUse)) 0
675 continue; 0
676 ----
677 // Check that the instruction is not a copy that partially overwrites the ----
678 // original copy source that we are about to use. The tracker mechanism ----
679 // cannot cope with that. ----
680 if (isCopyInstr(MI, *TII, UseCopyInstr) && 0
681 MI.modifiesRegister(CopySrcReg, TRI) && 0
682 !MI.definesRegister(CopySrcReg)) { 0
683 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "MCP: Copy source overlap with dest in " << MI); 0
684 continue; 0
685 } ----
686 ----
687 if (!DebugCounter::shouldExecute(FwdCounter)) { 0
688 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "MCP: Skipping forwarding due to debug counter:\n " 0
689 << MI); ----
690 continue; 0
691 } ----
692 ----
693 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "MCP: Replacing " << printReg(MOUse.getReg(), TRI) 0
694 << "\n with " << printReg(ForwardedReg, TRI) ----
695 << "\n in " << MI << " from " << *Copy); ----
696 ----
697 MOUse.setReg(ForwardedReg); 0
698 ----
699 if (!CopySrc.isRenamable()) 0
700 MOUse.setIsRenamable(false); 0
701 MOUse.setIsUndef(CopySrc.isUndef()); 0
702 ----
703 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "MCP: After replacement: " << MI << "\n"); 0
704 ----
705 // Clear kill markers that may have been invalidated. ----
706 for (MachineInstr &KMI : 0
707 make_range(Copy->getIterator(), std::next(MI.getIterator()))) 0
708 KMI.clearRegisterKills(CopySrcReg, TRI); 0
709 ----
710 ++NumCopyForwards; 0
711 Changed = true; 0
712 } ----
713 } ----
714 ----
715 void MachineCopyPropagation::ForwardCopyPropagateBlock(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
716 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "MCP: ForwardCopyPropagateBlock " << MBB.getName() 0
717 << "\n"); ----
718 ----
719 for (MachineInstr &MI : llvm::make_early_inc_range(MBB)) { 0
720 // Analyze copies (which don't overlap themselves). ----
721 std::optional CopyOperands = ----
722 isCopyInstr(MI, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
723 if (CopyOperands) { 0
724 ----
725 Register RegSrc = CopyOperands->Source->getReg(); 0
726 Register RegDef = CopyOperands->Destination->getReg(); 0
727 ----
728 if (!TRI->regsOverlap(RegDef, RegSrc)) { 0
729 assert(RegDef.isPhysical() && RegSrc.isPhysical() && 0
730 "MachineCopyPropagation should be run after register allocation!"); ----
731 ----
732 MCRegister Def = RegDef.asMCReg(); 0
733 MCRegister Src = RegSrc.asMCReg(); 0
734 ----
735 // The two copies cancel out and the source of the first copy ----
736 // hasn't been overridden, eliminate the second one. e.g. ----
737 // %ecx = COPY %eax ----
738 // ... nothing clobbered eax. ----
739 // %eax = COPY %ecx ----
740 // => ----
741 // %ecx = COPY %eax ----
742 // ----
743 // or ----
744 // ----
745 // %ecx = COPY %eax ----
746 // ... nothing clobbered eax. ----
747 // %ecx = COPY %eax ----
748 // => ----
749 // %ecx = COPY %eax ----
750 if (eraseIfRedundant(MI, Def, Src) || eraseIfRedundant(MI, Src, Def)) 0
751 continue; 0
752 ----
753 forwardUses(MI); 0
754 ----
755 // Src may have been changed by forwardUses() ----
756 CopyOperands = isCopyInstr(MI, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
757 Src = CopyOperands->Source->getReg().asMCReg(); 0
758 ----
759 // If Src is defined by a previous copy, the previous copy cannot be ----
760 // eliminated. ----
761 ReadRegister(Src, MI, RegularUse); 0
762 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.implicit_operands()) { 0
763 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.readsReg()) 0
764 continue; 0
765 MCRegister Reg = MO.getReg().asMCReg(); 0
766 if (!Reg) 0
767 continue; 0
768 ReadRegister(Reg, MI, RegularUse); 0
769 } ----
770 ----
771 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "MCP: Copy is a deletion candidate: "; MI.dump()); 0
772 ----
773 // Copy is now a candidate for deletion. ----
774 if (!MRI->isReserved(Def)) 0
775 MaybeDeadCopies.insert(&MI); 0
776 ----
777 // If 'Def' is previously source of another copy, then this earlier copy's ----
778 // source is no longer available. e.g. ----
779 // %xmm9 = copy %xmm2 ----
780 // ... ----
781 // %xmm2 = copy %xmm0 ----
782 // ... ----
783 // %xmm2 = copy %xmm9 ----
784 Tracker.clobberRegister(Def, *TRI, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
785 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.implicit_operands()) { 0
786 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.isDef()) 0
787 continue; 0
788 MCRegister Reg = MO.getReg().asMCReg(); 0
789 if (!Reg) 0
790 continue; 0
791 Tracker.clobberRegister(Reg, *TRI, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
792 } ----
793 ----
794 Tracker.trackCopy(&MI, *TRI, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
795 ----
796 continue; 0
797 } 0
798 } ----
799 ----
800 // Clobber any earlyclobber regs first. ----
801 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) 0
802 if (MO.isReg() && MO.isEarlyClobber()) { 0
803 MCRegister Reg = MO.getReg().asMCReg(); 0
804 // If we have a tied earlyclobber, that means it is also read by this ----
805 // instruction, so we need to make sure we don't remove it as dead ----
806 // later. ----
807 if (MO.isTied()) 0
808 ReadRegister(Reg, MI, RegularUse); 0
809 Tracker.clobberRegister(Reg, *TRI, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
810 } ----
811 ----
812 forwardUses(MI); 0
813 ----
814 // Not a copy. ----
815 SmallVector Defs; 0
816 const MachineOperand *RegMask = nullptr; 0
817 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
818 if (MO.isRegMask()) 0
819 RegMask = &MO; 0
820 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
821 continue; 0
822 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
823 if (!Reg) 0
824 continue; 0
825 ----
826 assert(!Reg.isVirtual() && 0
827 "MachineCopyPropagation should be run after register allocation!"); ----
828 ----
829 if (MO.isDef() && !MO.isEarlyClobber()) { 0
830 Defs.push_back(Reg.asMCReg()); 0
831 continue; 0
832 } else if (MO.readsReg()) 0
833 ReadRegister(Reg.asMCReg(), MI, MO.isDebug() ? DebugUse : RegularUse); 0
834 } ----
835 ----
836 // The instruction has a register mask operand which means that it clobbers ----
837 // a large set of registers. Treat clobbered registers the same way as ----
838 // defined registers. ----
839 if (RegMask) { 0
840 // Erase any MaybeDeadCopies whose destination register is clobbered. ----
841 for (SmallSetVector::iterator DI = 0
842 MaybeDeadCopies.begin(); 0
843 DI != MaybeDeadCopies.end();) { 0
844 MachineInstr *MaybeDead = *DI; 0
845 std::optional CopyOperands = ----
846 isCopyInstr(*MaybeDead, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
847 MCRegister Reg = CopyOperands->Destination->getReg().asMCReg(); 0
848 assert(!MRI->isReserved(Reg)); 0
849 ----
850 if (!RegMask->clobbersPhysReg(Reg)) { 0
851 ++DI; 0
852 continue; 0
853 } ----
854 ----
855 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "MCP: Removing copy due to regmask clobbering: "; 0
856 MaybeDead->dump()); ----
857 ----
858 // Make sure we invalidate any entries in the copy maps before erasing ----
859 // the instruction. ----
860 Tracker.clobberRegister(Reg, *TRI, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
861 ----
862 // erase() will return the next valid iterator pointing to the next ----
863 // element after the erased one. ----
864 DI = MaybeDeadCopies.erase(DI); 0
865 MaybeDead->eraseFromParent(); 0
866 Changed = true; 0
867 ++NumDeletes; 0
868 } ----
869 } ----
870 ----
871 // Any previous copy definition or reading the Defs is no longer available. ----
872 for (MCRegister Reg : Defs) 0
873 Tracker.clobberRegister(Reg, *TRI, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
874 } 0
875 ----
876 // If MBB doesn't have successors, delete the copies whose defs are not used. ----
877 // If MBB does have successors, then conservative assume the defs are live-out ----
878 // since we don't want to trust live-in lists. ----
879 if (MBB.succ_empty()) { 0
880 for (MachineInstr *MaybeDead : MaybeDeadCopies) { 0
881 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "MCP: Removing copy due to no live-out succ: "; 0
882 MaybeDead->dump()); ----
883 ----
884 std::optional CopyOperands = ----
885 isCopyInstr(*MaybeDead, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
886 assert(CopyOperands); 0
887 ----
888 Register SrcReg = CopyOperands->Source->getReg(); 0
889 Register DestReg = CopyOperands->Destination->getReg(); 0
890 assert(!MRI->isReserved(DestReg)); 0
891 ----
892 // Update matching debug values, if any. ----
893 SmallVector MaybeDeadDbgUsers( ----
894 CopyDbgUsers[MaybeDead].begin(), CopyDbgUsers[MaybeDead].end()); 0
895 MRI->updateDbgUsersToReg(DestReg.asMCReg(), SrcReg.asMCReg(), 0
896 MaybeDeadDbgUsers); ----
897 ----
898 MaybeDead->eraseFromParent(); 0
899 Changed = true; 0
900 ++NumDeletes; 0
901 } 0
902 } ----
903 ----
904 MaybeDeadCopies.clear(); 0
905 CopyDbgUsers.clear(); 0
906 Tracker.clear(); 0
907 } 0
908 ----
909 static bool isBackwardPropagatableCopy(const DestSourcePair &CopyOperands, 0
910 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI, ----
911 const TargetInstrInfo &TII) { ----
912 Register Def = CopyOperands.Destination->getReg(); 0
913 Register Src = CopyOperands.Source->getReg(); 0
914 ----
915 if (!Def || !Src) 0
916 return false; 0
917 ----
918 if (MRI.isReserved(Def) || MRI.isReserved(Src)) 0
919 return false; 0
920 ----
921 return CopyOperands.Source->isRenamable() && CopyOperands.Source->isKill(); 0
922 } ----
923 ----
924 void MachineCopyPropagation::propagateDefs(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
925 if (!Tracker.hasAnyCopies()) 0
926 return; 0
927 ----
928 for (unsigned OpIdx = 0, OpEnd = MI.getNumOperands(); OpIdx != OpEnd; 0
929 ++OpIdx) { ----
930 MachineOperand &MODef = MI.getOperand(OpIdx); 0
931 ----
932 if (!MODef.isReg() || MODef.isUse()) 0
933 continue; 0
934 ----
935 // Ignore non-trivial cases. ----
936 if (MODef.isTied() || MODef.isUndef() || MODef.isImplicit()) 0
937 continue; 0
938 ----
939 if (!MODef.getReg()) 0
940 continue; 0
941 ----
942 // We only handle if the register comes from a vreg. ----
943 if (!MODef.isRenamable()) 0
944 continue; 0
945 ----
946 MachineInstr *Copy = Tracker.findAvailBackwardCopy( 0
947 MI, MODef.getReg().asMCReg(), *TRI, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
948 if (!Copy) 0
949 continue; 0
950 ----
951 std::optional CopyOperands = ----
952 isCopyInstr(*Copy, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
953 Register Def = CopyOperands->Destination->getReg(); 0
954 Register Src = CopyOperands->Source->getReg(); 0
955 ----
956 if (MODef.getReg() != Src) 0
957 continue; 0
958 ----
959 if (!isBackwardPropagatableRegClassCopy(*Copy, MI, OpIdx)) 0
960 continue; 0
961 ----
962 if (hasImplicitOverlap(MI, MODef)) 0
963 continue; 0
964 ----
965 if (hasOverlappingMultipleDef(MI, MODef, Def)) 0
966 continue; 0
967 ----
968 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "MCP: Replacing " << printReg(MODef.getReg(), TRI) 0
969 << "\n with " << printReg(Def, TRI) << "\n in " ----
970 << MI << " from " << *Copy); ----
971 ----
972 MODef.setReg(Def); 0
973 MODef.setIsRenamable(CopyOperands->Destination->isRenamable()); 0
974 ----
975 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "MCP: After replacement: " << MI << "\n"); 0
976 MaybeDeadCopies.insert(Copy); 0
977 Changed = true; 0
978 ++NumCopyBackwardPropagated; 0
979 } ----
980 } ----
981 ----
982 void MachineCopyPropagation::BackwardCopyPropagateBlock( 0
983 MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { ----
984 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "MCP: BackwardCopyPropagateBlock " << MBB.getName() 0
985 << "\n"); ----
986 ----
987 for (MachineInstr &MI : llvm::make_early_inc_range(llvm::reverse(MBB))) { 0
988 // Ignore non-trivial COPYs. ----
989 std::optional CopyOperands = ----
990 isCopyInstr(MI, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
991 if (CopyOperands && MI.getNumOperands() == 2) { 0
992 Register DefReg = CopyOperands->Destination->getReg(); 0
993 Register SrcReg = CopyOperands->Source->getReg(); 0
994 ----
995 if (!TRI->regsOverlap(DefReg, SrcReg)) { 0
996 // Unlike forward cp, we don't invoke propagateDefs here, ----
997 // just let forward cp do COPY-to-COPY propagation. ----
998 if (isBackwardPropagatableCopy(*CopyOperands, *MRI, *TII)) { 0
999 Tracker.invalidateRegister(SrcReg.asMCReg(), *TRI, *TII, 0
1000 UseCopyInstr); 0
1001 Tracker.invalidateRegister(DefReg.asMCReg(), *TRI, *TII, 0
1002 UseCopyInstr); 0
1003 Tracker.trackCopy(&MI, *TRI, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
1004 continue; 0
1005 } ----
1006 } ----
1007 } ----
1008 ----
1009 // Invalidate any earlyclobber regs first. ----
1010 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) 0
1011 if (MO.isReg() && MO.isEarlyClobber()) { 0
1012 MCRegister Reg = MO.getReg().asMCReg(); 0
1013 if (!Reg) 0
1014 continue; 0
1015 Tracker.invalidateRegister(Reg, *TRI, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
1016 } ----
1017 ----
1018 propagateDefs(MI); 0
1019 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
1020 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
1021 continue; 0
1022 ----
1023 if (!MO.getReg()) 0
1024 continue; 0
1025 ----
1026 if (MO.isDef()) 0
1027 Tracker.invalidateRegister(MO.getReg().asMCReg(), *TRI, *TII, 0
1028 UseCopyInstr); 0
1029 ----
1030 if (MO.readsReg()) { 0
1031 if (MO.isDebug()) { 0
1032 // Check if the register in the debug instruction is utilized ----
1033 // in a copy instruction, so we can update the debug info if the ----
1034 // register is changed. ----
1035 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI->regunits(MO.getReg().asMCReg())) { 0
1036 if (auto *Copy = Tracker.findCopyDefViaUnit(Unit, *TRI)) { 0
1037 CopyDbgUsers[Copy].insert(&MI); 0
1038 } ----
1039 } ----
1040 } else { ----
1041 Tracker.invalidateRegister(MO.getReg().asMCReg(), *TRI, *TII, 0
1042 UseCopyInstr); 0
1043 } ----
1044 } ----
1045 } ----
1046 } ----
1047 ----
1048 for (auto *Copy : MaybeDeadCopies) { 0
1049 std::optional CopyOperands = ----
1050 isCopyInstr(*Copy, *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
1051 Register Src = CopyOperands->Source->getReg(); 0
1052 Register Def = CopyOperands->Destination->getReg(); 0
1053 SmallVector MaybeDeadDbgUsers(CopyDbgUsers[Copy].begin(), 0
1054 CopyDbgUsers[Copy].end()); 0
1055 ----
1056 MRI->updateDbgUsersToReg(Src.asMCReg(), Def.asMCReg(), MaybeDeadDbgUsers); 0
1057 Copy->eraseFromParent(); 0
1058 ++NumDeletes; 0
1059 } 0
1060 ----
1061 MaybeDeadCopies.clear(); 0
1062 CopyDbgUsers.clear(); 0
1063 Tracker.clear(); 0
1064 } 0
1065 ----
1066 static void LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED printSpillReloadChain( 0
1067 DenseMap> &SpillChain, ----
1068 DenseMap> &ReloadChain, ----
1069 MachineInstr *Leader) { ----
1070 auto &SC = SpillChain[Leader]; 0
1071 auto &RC = ReloadChain[Leader]; 0
1072 for (auto I = SC.rbegin(), E = SC.rend(); I != E; ++I) 0
1073 (*I)->dump(); 0
1074 for (MachineInstr *MI : RC) 0
1075 MI->dump(); 0
1076 } 0
1077 ----
1078 // Remove spill-reload like copy chains. For example ----
1079 // r0 = COPY r1 ----
1080 // r1 = COPY r2 ----
1081 // r2 = COPY r3 ----
1082 // r3 = COPY r4 ----
1083 // ----
1084 // r4 = COPY r3 ----
1085 // r3 = COPY r2 ----
1086 // r2 = COPY r1 ----
1087 // r1 = COPY r0 ----
1088 // will be folded into ----
1089 // r0 = COPY r1 ----
1090 // r1 = COPY r4 ----
1091 // ----
1092 // r4 = COPY r1 ----
1093 // r1 = COPY r0 ----
1094 // TODO: Currently we don't track usage of r0 outside the chain, so we ----
1095 // conservatively keep its value as it was before the rewrite. ----
1096 // ----
1097 // The algorithm is trying to keep ----
1098 // property#1: No Def of spill COPY in the chain is used or defined until the ----
1099 // paired reload COPY in the chain uses the Def. ----
1100 // ----
1101 // property#2: NO Source of COPY in the chain is used or defined until the next ----
1102 // COPY in the chain defines the Source, except the innermost spill-reload ----
1103 // pair. ----
1104 // ----
1105 // The algorithm is conducted by checking every COPY inside the MBB, assuming ----
1106 // the COPY is a reload COPY, then try to find paired spill COPY by searching ----
1107 // the COPY defines the Src of the reload COPY backward. If such pair is found, ----
1108 // it either belongs to an existing chain or a new chain depends on ----
1109 // last available COPY uses the Def of the reload COPY. ----
1110 // Implementation notes, we use CopyTracker::findLastDefCopy(Reg, ...) to find ----
1111 // out last COPY that defines Reg; we use CopyTracker::findLastUseCopy(Reg, ...) ----
1112 // to find out last COPY that uses Reg. When we are encountered with a Non-COPY ----
1113 // instruction, we check registers in the operands of this instruction. If this ----
1114 // Reg is defined by a COPY, we untrack this Reg via ----
1115 // CopyTracker::clobberRegister(Reg, ...). ----
1116 void MachineCopyPropagation::EliminateSpillageCopies(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
1117 // ChainLeader maps MI inside a spill-reload chain to its innermost reload COPY. ----
1118 // Thus we can track if a MI belongs to an existing spill-reload chain. ----
1119 DenseMap ChainLeader; 0
1120 // SpillChain maps innermost reload COPY of a spill-reload chain to a sequence ----
1121 // of COPYs that forms spills of a spill-reload chain. ----
1122 // ReloadChain maps innermost reload COPY of a spill-reload chain to a ----
1123 // sequence of COPYs that forms reloads of a spill-reload chain. ----
1124 DenseMap> SpillChain, ReloadChain; 0
1125 // If a COPY's Source has use or def until next COPY defines the Source, ----
1126 // we put the COPY in this set to keep property#2. ----
1127 DenseSet CopySourceInvalid; 0
1128 ----
1129 auto TryFoldSpillageCopies = ----
1130 [&, this](const SmallVectorImpl &SC, 0
1131 const SmallVectorImpl &RC) { 0
1132 assert(SC.size() == RC.size() && "Spill-reload should be paired"); 0
1133 ----
1134 // We need at least 3 pairs of copies for the transformation to apply, ----
1135 // because the first outermost pair cannot be removed since we don't ----
1136 // recolor outside of the chain and that we need at least one temporary ----
1137 // spill slot to shorten the chain. If we only have a chain of two ----
1138 // pairs, we already have the shortest sequence this code can handle: ----
1139 // the outermost pair for the temporary spill slot, and the pair that ----
1140 // use that temporary spill slot for the other end of the chain. ----
1141 // TODO: We might be able to simplify to one spill-reload pair if collecting ----
1142 // more infomation about the outermost COPY. ----
1143 if (SC.size() <= 2) 0
1144 return; 0
1145 ----
1146 // If violate property#2, we don't fold the chain. ----
1147 for (const MachineInstr *Spill : make_range(SC.begin() + 1, SC.end())) 0
1148 if (CopySourceInvalid.count(Spill)) 0
1149 return; 0
1150 ----
1151 for (const MachineInstr *Reload : make_range(RC.begin(), RC.end() - 1)) 0
1152 if (CopySourceInvalid.count(Reload)) 0
1153 return; 0
1154 ----
1155 auto CheckCopyConstraint = [this](Register Def, Register Src) { 0
1156 for (const TargetRegisterClass *RC : TRI->regclasses()) { 0
1157 if (RC->contains(Def) && RC->contains(Src)) 0
1158 return true; 0
1159 } ----
1160 return false; 0
1161 }; 0
1162 ----
1163 auto UpdateReg = [](MachineInstr *MI, const MachineOperand *Old, 0
1164 const MachineOperand *New) { ----
1165 for (MachineOperand &MO : MI->operands()) { 0
1166 if (&MO == Old) 0
1167 MO.setReg(New->getReg()); 0
1168 } ----
1169 }; 0
1170 ----
1171 std::optional InnerMostSpillCopy = ----
1172 isCopyInstr(*SC[0], *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
1173 std::optional OuterMostSpillCopy = ----
1174 isCopyInstr(*SC.back(), *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
1175 std::optional InnerMostReloadCopy = ----
1176 isCopyInstr(*RC[0], *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
1177 std::optional OuterMostReloadCopy = ----
1178 isCopyInstr(*RC.back(), *TII, UseCopyInstr); 0
1179 if (!CheckCopyConstraint(OuterMostSpillCopy->Source->getReg(), 0
1180 InnerMostSpillCopy->Source->getReg()) || 0
1181 !CheckCopyConstraint(InnerMostReloadCopy->Destination->getReg(), 0
1182 OuterMostReloadCopy->Destination->getReg())) 0
1183 return; 0
1184 ----
1185 SpillageChainsLength += SC.size() + RC.size(); 0
1186 NumSpillageChains += 1; 0
1187 UpdateReg(SC[0], InnerMostSpillCopy->Destination, 0
1188 OuterMostSpillCopy->Source); 0
1189 UpdateReg(RC[0], InnerMostReloadCopy->Source, 0
1190 OuterMostReloadCopy->Destination); 0
1191 ----

10 // 10 //
11 // This pass forwards the source of COPYs to the users of their destinations 11 // This pass forwards the source of COPYs to the users of their destinations
12 // when doing so is legal. For example: 12 // when doing so is legal. For example:
13 // 13 //
14 // %reg1 = COPY %reg0 14 // %reg1 = COPY %reg0
15 // ... 15 // ...
16 // ... = OP %reg1 16 // ... = OP %reg1
17 // 17 //
18 // If 18 // If
19 // - %reg0 has not been clobbered by the time of the use of %reg1 19 // - %reg0 has not been clobbered by the time of the use of %reg1
20 // - the register class constraints are satisfied 20 // - the register class constraints are satisfied
21 // - the COPY def is the only value that reaches OP 21 // - the COPY def is the only value that reaches OP
22 // then this pass replaces the above with: 22 // then this pass replaces the above with:
23 // 23 //
24 // %reg1 = COPY %reg0 24 // %reg1 = COPY %reg0
25 // ... 25 // ...
26 // ... = OP %reg0 26 // ... = OP %reg0
27 // 27 //
28 // This pass also removes some redundant COPYs. For example: 28 // This pass also removes some redundant COPYs. For example:
29 // 29 //
30 // %R1 = COPY %R0 30 // %R1 = COPY %R0
31 // ... // No clobber of %R1 31 // ... // No clobber of %R1
32 // %R0 = COPY %R1 <<< Removed 32 // %R0 = COPY %R1 <<< Removed
33 // 33 //
34 // or 34 // or
35 // 35 //
36 // %R1 = COPY %R0 36 // %R1 = COPY %R0
